Students engage in a comprehensive study of the family, social institutions, and cultural variations. Sociology prepares students for college level studies and provides them with a better understanding of society. This course contains mature content. NOTE: This course involves sensitive issues that are presented appropriately for the age level. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0355VIRF', 'AP Microeconomics - VirSup(Fall)', 0.5, 5, 'Social Studies', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'This course satisfies the Economics high school graduation requirement.', 'This one-semester course gives students a thorough understanding of the principles of economics that apply to functions of individual decision makers, both consumers and producers, within the economic system, with an emphasis on the nature and functions of product markets. This course also includes the study of factor markets and the role of government in promoting greater efficiency and equity in the economy. Students enrolled in an Advanced Placement course are expected to take the corresponding AP exam. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0366VIRF', 'SS Research Methods KAP A&B - VirSup(Fall)', 0.5, 5, 'Social Studies', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, 'Fall registration for the AP Psychology exam is recommended for students taking Social Studies Research Methods KAP in the fall semester. INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('0505VIRF', 'Health Education - VirSup(Fall)', 0.5, 4, 'Health', 'Semester 1', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'This course is designed to empower students to make healthy choices for their physical, mental, and social well-being. Key topics include nutrition and fitness, stress management, personal safety, disease prevention, substance use awareness, and building positive relationships. Students will also practice decision-making and goal-setting skills that support lifelong health. By the end of the course, students will be better prepared to care for themselves and make responsible choices for a healthy future. NOTE: Parental consent must be provided for students to participate in lessons on human sexuality, child abuse, sex trafficking, dating violence, and family violence. Katy ISD follows an abstinence-only approach in its Health curriculum. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('1706A', 'College Prep English', 0.5, 4, 'English Language Arts', 'Semester 1', '0101VIRA', NULL, 'This course may be required for students who do not meet college readiness standards. This course satisfies the required FHSPE fourth English credit if the student has earned credit for English 1, English 2, and English 3 and graduates the same school year that College Prep English is successfully completed.', 'College Prep English is designed for 12th grade students whose coursework, EOC scores, or college entrance exams (PSAT, ACT, SAT, TSIA, etc.) indicate that the student would benefit from further preparation for college -level coursework in English. This cou rse prepares students for success in entry -level college courses and/or success on the Texas Success Initiative Assessment (TSIA). This is a rigorous course that will include student learning outcomes and objectives th at include the principles of grammar, usage, and mechanics and utilizes the writing process to teach students to write formal essays and to address a variety of topics with multiple approaches. Can be taken as an Elective.') ON CONFLICT (course_code) DO NOTHING

INSERT INTO courses (course_code, course_name, credits, gpa, subject, term, prerequisite_text, corequisite_text, enrollment_notes, course_description) VALUES ('1707A', 'College Prep Math', 0.5, 4, 'Math', 'Semester 1', '0211A or 0223A', NULL, 'This course may be required for students who do not meet college readiness standards.
